-- Russia Says Seven Kidnapped in Nigeria, Ransom Request Expected
-- B y   S t e p a n   K r a v c h e n k o
-- 2012-10-17T18:09:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-17/russia-says-seven-kidnapped-in-nigeria-ransom-request-expected.html
Six Russian sailors and an Estonian
national were abducted by pirates in Nigerian waters, the
Russian Foreign Affairs Ministry said today on its website.  The pirates escaped into Nigerian territory after the
kidnapping two days ago, and are likely to demand a ransom, the
ministry said. It said  Russia  is attempting to secure a swift
release for the sailors.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stepan Kravchenko in Moscow at 
 skravchenko@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
